===Proper noun===
'''Abel'''

# According to the [[Bible]], the son of [[Adam]] and [[Eve]] who was killed by his brother [[Cain]].

===Etymology===
From Hebrew (habel) = 'wind, air; vanity', from Assyrian (habel, habal = 'son').

